{"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","role":"article","title":"Decorations"},"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/Navigator","doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/Preferences","doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/SwiftUI","doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/Input","doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/Highlights","doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/EPUB-Fonts"],"title":"Essentials","anchor":"Essentials","generated":true}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/Decorations","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"text":"The Decoration API lets you overlay visual elements on publication content – highlights, search result markers, TTS playback indicators, page-number labels in the margin, and more. For the common case of implementing user highlights, see the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"Highlights.md","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"overview","level":2,"text":"Overview"},{"type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"[!NOTE]","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Only ","type":"text"},{"code":"EPUBNavigatorViewController","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" implements ","type":"text"},{"code":"DecorableNavigator","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" today. Always check if a navigator implements ","type":"text"},{"code":"DecorableNavigator","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" before enabling decoration-dependent features to future-proof your code.","type":"text"}]}],"name":"Note"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Overview","level":2,"text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The Decoration API is built around a small set of types that work together."}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Decoration","level":3,"text":"Decoration"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Decoration"},{"type":"text","text":" is a single UI element overlaid on publication content. It pairs a "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"location","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Locator"},{"type":"text","text":") with a "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"style","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Decoration.Style"},{"type":"text","text":") and carries a stable "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"id"},{"type":"text","text":" used to track changes across updates."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A single logical entity can map to multiple Decoration objects. For example, a user annotation might use one decoration for the highlight and a second for a margin icon at the same location."}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Decoration-Style","level":3,"text":"Decoration Style"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"code":"Decoration.Style","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" describes the ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"abstract appearance","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" of a decoration — for example, a semi-transparent highlight or an underline — independently of the underlying media type or rendering engine. The toolkit ships two built-in styles (","type":"text"},{"code":"highlight","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"underline","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":") and lets you define your own  via ","type":"text"},{"code":"Decoration.Style.Id","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Decoration-Template-EPUB","level":4,"text":"Decoration Template (EPUB)"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For EPUB, each ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Decoration.Style.Id"},{"text":" maps to an ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"HTMLDecorationTemplate"},{"text":" that translates the abstract style into concrete HTML\/CSS injected into the page.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Decoration-Group","level":3,"text":"Decoration Group"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Decorations are organised into ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"named groups","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":", one per logical app feature (e.g. ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"highlights"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"search"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"tts"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"page-list"},{"text":", etc.). Each call to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"apply(decorations:in:)"},{"text":" declares the complete desired state of one group; groups are fully independent. The navigator diffs the new list against the previous one internally and pushes only the necessary changes to the rendered content, so you can call ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"apply"},{"text":" on every state change without worrying about performance.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Guides","level":2,"text":"Guides"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Creating-a-Decoration","level":3,"text":"Creating a Decoration"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"code":"Decoration","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" pairs a location in the publication with a style to render. The ","type":"text"},{"code":"id","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" must be unique within the group and should match your model’s primary key—this is what lets you look up the underlying record when the user taps the decoration later.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["let decoration = Decoration(","    id: highlight.id,","    locator: highlight.locator,","    style: .highlight(tint: highlight.color)",")"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Applying-Decorations-to-the-Navigator","level":3,"text":"Applying Decorations to the Navigator"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Rather than telling the navigator about individual additions or removals, you declare the complete desired state of a group and let the navigator figure out what changed. Observe your models, map each one to a ","type":"text"},{"code":"Decoration","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", then apply the full list:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["let decorations = highlights.map { highlight in","    Decoration(","        id: highlight.id,","        locator: highlight.locator,","        style: .highlight(tint: highlight.color)","    )","}","","navigator.apply(decorations: decorations, in: \"highlights\")"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The navigator diffs the new list against the previous one and pushes only the actual changes to the rendered content. This means you can call ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"apply"},{"text":" freely on every state change — after an add, a color update, or a delete — without worrying about redundant work.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To clear a group entirely, apply an empty array:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["navigator.apply(decorations: [], in: \"highlights\")"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Handling-User-Interactions-on-Decorations","level":3,"text":"Handling User Interactions on Decorations"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Register a callback with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"observeDecorationInteractions(inGroup:onActivated:)"},{"type":"text","text":" to be notified when the user taps a decoration. The event carries the decoration itself, its group name, and the tap location in navigator view coordinates:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["navigator.observeDecorationInteractions(inGroup: \"highlights\") { event in","","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"code":"event.decoration.id","type":"codeVoice"}]},{"text":" matches the id you set when creating the Decoration, so you can retrieve the corresponding model from your database.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"code":"event.rect","type":"codeVoice"}]},{"type":"text","text":" gives the bounding box of the tapped decoration in the navigator view, useful for anchoring a popover."}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Checking-Whether-a-Navigator-Supports-a-Decoration-Style","level":3,"text":"Checking Whether a Navigator Supports a Decoration Style"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Not every navigator can render every style — underlining a sentence in an audiobook, for example, makes no sense. Before enabling a feature that depends on a specific style, verify that the navigator supports it:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["if navigator.supports(decorationStyle: .underline) {","    \/\/ Offer underlining in the UI","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"EPUBNavigatorViewController"},{"type":"text","text":", this returns "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":" for any style ID present in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Configuration.decorationTemplates"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Creating-a-Custom-Decoration-Style","level":3,"text":"Creating a Custom Decoration Style"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The following example shows how to add a page-number label in the left margin for each entry in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"publication.pageList"},{"type":"text","text":" (declared print page markers)."}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"1-Declare-a-custom-DecorationStyleId","level":4,"text":"1. Declare a custom `Decoration.Style.Id`"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["extension Decoration.Style.Id {","    static let pageList: Decoration.Style.Id = \"page-list\"","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"2-Define-a-config-struct","level":4,"text":"2. Define a config struct"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The config carries the data your template needs. It must be ","type":"text"},{"code":"Hashable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" so the diffing engine can detect changes.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["struct PageListConfig: Hashable {","    \/\/\/ Page number label from publication.pageList[].title","    var label: String   ","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"3-Write-the-HTMLDecorationTemplate","level":4,"text":"3. Write the `HTMLDecorationTemplate`"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["extension HTMLDecorationTemplate {","    static var pageList: HTMLDecorationTemplate {","        let className = \"app-page-number\"","","        return HTMLDecorationTemplate(","            \/\/ One rectangle for the whole range","            layout: .bounds,    ","            \/\/ Span the full page so the label can float left","            width: .page, ","            element: { decoration in","                let config = decoration.style.config as? PageListConfig","","                \/\/ var(--RS__backgroundColor) matches the Readium CSS theme background.","                \/\/ Setting it inline prevents it being forced transparent by Readium CSS.","                return \"\"\"","                    <div>","                        <span class=\"\\(className)\" style=\"background-color: var(--RS__backgroundColor) !important\">","                            \\(config?.label ?? \"\")","                        <\/span>","                    <\/div>","                \"\"\"","            },","            stylesheet: \"\"\"","                .\\(className) {","                    float: left;","                    margin-left: 4px;","                    padding: 0px 2px 0px 2px;","                    border: 1px solid;","                    border-radius: 10%;","                    box-shadow: rgba(50, 50, 93, 0.25) 0px 2px 5px -1px, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3) 0px 1px 3px -1px;","                    opacity: 0.8;","                }","            \"\"\"","        )","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"4-Register-it-in-ConfigurationdecorationTemplates","level":4,"text":"4. Register it in `Configuration.decorationTemplates`"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["var templates = HTMLDecorationTemplate.defaultTemplates()","templates[.pageList] = .pageList","","let navigator = try EPUBNavigatorViewController(","    publication: publication,","    initialLocation: lastReadLocation,","    config: EPUBNavigatorViewController.Configuration(","        decorationTemplates: templates","    )",")"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"5-Build-and-apply-decorations","level":4,"text":"5. Build and apply decorations"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["private func updatePageListDecorations() async {","    guard let navigator = navigator as? DecorableNavigator else { return }","","    var decorations: [Decoration] = []","    for (index, link) in publication.pageList.enumerated() {","        guard","            let title = link.title,","            let locator = await publication.locate(link)","        else {","            continue","        }","","        decorations.append(Decoration(","            id: \"page-list-\\(index)\",","            locator: locator,","            style: Decoration.Style(","                id: .pageList,","                config: PageListConfig(label: title)","            )","        ))","    }","","    navigator.apply(decorations: decorations, in: \"page-list\")","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Common-Patterns","level":3,"text":"Common Patterns"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Search-Results","level":4,"text":"Search Results"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Apply a temporary ","type":"text"},{"code":"\"search\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" group when the user performs a search. Use index-based IDs and ","type":"text"},{"code":"isActive","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to highlight the currently selected result. Clear the group when the search is dismissed.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["let navigator: DecorableNavigator","","func applySearchDecorations(selectedIndex: Int?) {","    let decorations = searchResults.enumerated().map { index, result in","        Decoration(","            id: \"\\(index)\",","            locator: result.locator,","            style: .highlight(isActive: index == selectedIndex)","        )","    }","    navigator.apply(decorations: decorations, in: \"search\")","}","","\/\/ Show all results with none selected","applySearchDecorations(selectedIndex: nil)","","\/\/ When the user moves to a result, mark it as active","applySearchDecorations(selectedIndex: currentResultIndex)","","\/\/ Clear on dismiss","navigator.apply(decorations: [], in: \"search\")"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"TTS-Playback","level":4,"text":"TTS Playback"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Track the currently spoken sentence with a single-decoration ","type":"text"},{"code":"\"tts\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" group. Replace the decoration each time TTS advances, and clear it when TTS stops.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["let navigator: DecorableNavigator","","func ttsDidStartSpeaking(locator: Locator) {","    let decoration = Decoration(","        id: \"tts\",","        locator: locator,","        style: .underline(tint: .red)","    )","    navigator.apply(decorations: [decoration], in: \"tts\")","}","","func ttsDidStop() {","    navigator.apply(decorations: [], in: \"tts\")","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Further-Reading","level":2,"text":"Further Reading"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/readium.org\/architecture\/proposals\/008-decorator-api.html","isActive":true}]}]}]}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium","doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/NavigatorOverview"]]},"kind":"article","references":{"doc://Readium/documentation/Readium/Preferences":{"title":"Configuring the Navigator","url":"\/documentation\/readium\/preferences","abstract":[{"text":"Take a look at the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"..\/Migration%20Guide.md","type":"reference"},{"text":" if you are already using the legacy EPUB settings.","type":"text"}],"kind":"article","role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/Preferences","type":"topic"},"../Migration%20Guide.md":{"identifier":"..\/Migration%20Guide.md","title":"migration guide","url":"..\/Migration%20Guide.md","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"migration guide"}]},"doc://Readium/documentation/Readium/Input":{"title":"Observing user input","identifier":"doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/Input","type":"topic","kind":"article","role":"article","url":"\/documentation\/readium\/input","abstract":[{"text":"In visual publications like EPUB or PDF, users can interact with the ","type":"text"},{"code":"VisualNavigator","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance using gestures, a keyboard, a mouse, a pencil, or a trackpad. When the publication does not override user input events, you may want to intercept them to trigger actions in your user interface. For example, you can turn pages or toggle the navigation bar on taps, or open a bookmarks screen when pressing the Command-Shift-D hotkey.","type":"text"}]},"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/swiftui/uiviewrepresentable":{"type":"link","url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/uiviewrepresentable","title":"UIViewRepresentable","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/uiviewrepresentable","titleInlineContent":[{"code":"UIViewRepresentable","type":"codeVoice"}]},"Decorations.md":{"identifier":"Decorations.md","title":"Decorations guide","url":"Decorations.md","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Decorations guide"}]},"Preferences.md":{"type":"link","url":"Preferences.md","title":"EPUB navigator preferences","identifier":"Preferences.md","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"EPUB navigator preferences","type":"text"}]},"doc://Readium/documentation/Readium/SwiftUI":{"url":"\/documentation\/readium\/swiftui","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"The Navigator is built with UIKit and provides ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UIViewController"},{"text":" implementations. Nevertheless, you can integrate them into a SwiftUI view hierarchy using Apple’s ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/uiviewrepresentable","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/SwiftUI","kind":"article","title":"Integrating the Navigator with SwiftUI"},"doc://Readium/documentation/Readium/Navigator":{"url":"\/documentation\/readium\/navigator","identifier":"doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/Navigator","kind":"article","role":"article","title":"Navigator","abstract":[{"text":"You can use a Readium Navigator to present the publication to the user. The ","type":"text"},{"code":"Navigator","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" renders resources on the screen and offers APIs and user interactions for navigating the contents.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic"},"doc://Readium/documentation/Readium":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The Readium Swift Toolkit is a toolkit for ebooks, audiobooks, and comics written in Swift & Kotlin."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium","title":"Readium","kind":"article","role":"collection","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/readium"},"doc://Readium/documentation/Readium/NavigatorOverview":{"url":"\/documentation\/readium\/navigatoroverview","title":"Navigator Overview","kind":"article","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn about the architecture, configuration, and usage of the Readium Navigator."}],"role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/NavigatorOverview"},"doc://Readium/documentation/Readium/EPUB-Fonts":{"type":"topic","title":"Font families in the EPUB navigator","kind":"article","role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/EPUB-Fonts","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Readium allows users to customize the font family used to render a reflowable EPUB, by changing the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"Preferences.md","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"url":"\/documentation\/readium\/epub-fonts"},"https://readium.org/architecture/proposals/008-decorator-api.html":{"identifier":"https:\/\/readium.org\/architecture\/proposals\/008-decorator-api.html","title":"Readium Decorator API proposal","url":"https:\/\/readium.org\/architecture\/proposals\/008-decorator-api.html","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Readium Decorator API proposal"}]},"doc://Readium/documentation/Readium/Highlights":{"title":"Implementing Highlights","url":"\/documentation\/readium\/highlights","abstract":[{"text":"Highlighting lets users mark up passages in a publication for later reference - a core feature of any reading app. In Readium, highlights are built on top of the ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Decoration API"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":". If you want to understand that API in depth or build a custom decoration style, see the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"Decorations.md"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"kind":"article","role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/Highlights","type":"topic"}}}